The project aims at promoting the modernization of the Brazilian courts, through the production of subsidies to the reform process of the Brazilian judiciary.branch, 
The project is divided into four main strands:
1) The preparation and review of legislative reform bills in the field of ​​Justice, as well as studies and seminars to promote the reform process of the judiciary branch;
2) The implementation of practices aimed at expanding access and improving the formal administration of the Brazilian justice system;
3) The implementation of extra-judicial mechanisms, which complement the actions and activities to strengthen the Brazilian formal justice system;
4) The institutional strengthening of the Secretariat of the Judicial Reform, primarily by training its staff, so that it can adequately fulfill its mission of fostering and coordinating the process of reform of the judiciary branch.

